parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spotted mirror glass can obstruct the driver's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The mirror glass has spots or imperfections
making it difficult to see other vehicles or pedestrians

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high beam/low beam dimmer switch can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The high beam and low beam headlights do not switch properly
the headlights are stuck on high or low beam
the headlights do not turn on at all
the dimmer switch is unresponsive or stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal switch can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to confusion for other drivers and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The turn signals do not function properly
the turn signals are stuck on or off
the turn signal lever is unresponsive or stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause leaks, electrical problems, and reduced visibility due to fogged windows, which can lead to accidents or discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The air conditioning blows warm air
the air conditioning makes a loud noise
the air conditioning has a burning smell
the air conditioning electrical components malfunction
